warning.text:
If you are using 1.19, 1.19.1, 1.19.2, or 1.19.3 you can safely ignore the "made for a newer version of Minecraft" warning when applying your resource pack in-game, as it is incorrect.
(If you are using 1.19.4, you won't see this warning.)

Although marked as incompatible, selecting all Zombie skins enables randomized variants when using mods such as OptiFine, or other alternatives that enable both random entity textures and custom entity models. This only works when selecting ALL packs in this category.

warning.text: These packs use a different method of connecting textures than in mods you might be used to such as OptiFine. They use a cullfacing method which means the connecting textures will connect to all blocks, not just themselves. This isn't a bug; it's an unintended and unresolvable side effect of this vanilla method.

packs.name: MobSpawnIndicator
packs.description:
Places crosses on blocks where hostile mobs are able to spawn.

No cross: Safe from hostile mob spawns.
Yellow: Spiders stay hostile and Zombies stop burning, even in the daylight.
Orange: Slimes can spawn (in slime chunks), and Blazes can spawn from spawners.
Red: All hostile mobs can spawn.

Turn Smooth Lighting OFF for the best results!
May run into rendering issues when using with the Sodium or OptiFine mods.
